House Resolution 426
By: Representatives Schofield of the 63rd, Jackson of the 68th, Davis of the 87th, Cannon of
the 58th, Burnough of the 77th, and others
A RESOLUTION
1 Urging the General Assembly to support the creation of a Black Maternal Health Caucus; and
2 for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, the United States has one of the highest rates of maternal mortality among
4 high-income countries, with approximately 700 to 900 pregnancy related deaths per year; and
5 WHEREAS, the United States Centers for Disease Control and Prevention estimates that 80
6 percent of pregnancy related deaths in the United States are preventable; and
7 WHEREAS, the United States has one of the highest infant mortality rates among
8 high-income countries, currently ranking 33 out of 36 countries belonging to the
9 Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development (OECD), with an average of 5.58
10 deaths per 1,000 live births; and
11 WHEREAS, there is a growing body of evidence that racism and racial bias in healthcare
12 systems contribute to the national maternal mortality and morbidity crisis and infant
13 mortality and morbidity, in particular for Black pregnant and postpartum women and infants;
14 and
